20	#RecommenderStatusChangedToUnderConsideration	default	%(appname)s: Revised version	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  The authors of the preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> and submitted by\r\n  %(articleAuthors)s have posted their revised version and their replies to your\r\n  comments and those of the reviewers. They may also have uploaded (as a PDF or\r\n  Word file) a revised version of their preprint, with the modifications\r\n  indicated in TrackChanges mode and a clean version of their PDF at this\r\n  address <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> (see also attachments in\r\n  this email).\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  For this new round of evaluation, you must reach a decision to ‘Revise’,\r\n  ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the article.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Please send us a message at %(mailManagers)s within one week – i.e. before\r\n  %(deadline)s –\r\n  <b\r\n    >to let us know whether you wish to send it out again for peer review or\r\n    whether you will make your decision without further review within the next\r\n    10 days</b\r\n  >\r\n  (and preferentially within a week). If you need more time, please let us know\r\n  by return mail.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Finally, note that we asked the authors to make the following compulsory\r\n  changes on their article. We would be happy if you could check that they have\r\n  been done:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  1) Data must be available to readers after recommendation, either in the text\r\n  or through an open data repository such as Zenodo (free), Dryad (to pay) or\r\n  some other institutional repository. Data must be reusable, thus metadata or\r\n  accompanying text must carefully describe the data;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  2) Details on quantitative analyses (e.g., data treatment and statistical\r\n  scripts in R, bioinformatic pipeline scripts, etc.) and details concerning\r\n  simulations (scripts, codes) must be available to readers in the text, as\r\n  appendices, or through an open data repository, such as Zenodo, Dryad or some\r\n  other institutional repository. The scripts or codes must be carefully\r\n  described so that they can be reused;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  3) Details on experimental procedures must be available to readers in the text\r\n  or as appendices;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  4) Authors must have no financial conflict of interest relating to the\r\n  article. The article must contain a "Conflict of interest disclosure"\r\n  paragraph before the reference section containing this sentence: "The authors\r\n  of this article declare that they have no financial conflict of interest with\r\n  the content of this article.";\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  5) This disclosure has to be completed by a sentence indicating that some of\r\n  the authors are PCI recommenders: “XY is one of the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> recommenders.”\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We look forward to your decision. Thanks in advance!\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
21	#RecommenderStatusChangedUnderToRecommended	default	%(appname)s: Article recommended	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  Your recommendation - along with the reviews - is now posted on the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="%(doiRecomm)s">%(doiRecomm)s</a></p>\r\n<p>And there: <a href="%(linkRecomm)s">%(linkRecomm)s</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You will find the reference to your recommendation and that of the recommended\r\n  article.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you\r\n  are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc...\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for recommending this article for <i>%(appname)s</i>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
22	#RecommenderSuggestedArticle	default	%(appname)s: Request to act as a recommender for a preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  You have been suggested as a recommender for a preprint entitled\r\n  <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s (DOI %(articleDoi)s). You can\r\n  obtain information about this request and accept or decline this invitation by\r\n  following this link <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging\r\n  on to the <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Requests for input —> Do\r\n  you agree to initiate a recommendation?' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  <b\r\n    >Important information before accepting to become the recommender for this\r\n    preprint:</b\r\n  >\r\n  The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding\r\n  reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews),\r\n  and may lead to the recommendation of the preprint after several rounds of\r\n  reviews. The evaluation forms the basis of the decision to ‘Revise’,\r\n  ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint. A preprint recommended by\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘classic’\r\n  articles published in peer-reviewed journals. Details about the recommendation\r\n  process can be found <a href="%(helpurl)s">here</a>. You can also watch this\r\n  short video:\r\n  <a href="https://youtu.be/u5greO-q8-M">\r\n    How to start and manage a preprint recommendation</a\r\n  >.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Agreeing to become the recommender for this preprint means that\r\n  <b>you find the preprint interesting</b> and therefore worth sending out for\r\n  peer-review. Then, you will need to meet the following\r\n  <b>requirements</b>:<br />\r\n  1-\r\n  <b>\r\n    to send invitations to 5-10 potential reviewers within the next 24 hours\r\n  </b>\r\n  and then to send reminders and/or new invitations until you find at least two\r\n  reviewers willing to review the preprint. This process of finding reviews\r\n  should take no more than a week.<br />\r\n  2- <b>to post your decision</b> or to write your recommendation text\r\n  <b>within 10 days</b> of receiving the reviews.<br />\r\n  3- <b>to write a recommendation text</b> if you decide to recommend this\r\n  preprint for <i>%(appname)s</i> at the end of the evaluation process. Indeed,\r\n  if after one or several rounds of review, you decide to recommend this\r\n  preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation” that will have its own DOI\r\n  and be published by <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND. The\r\n  recommendation is a short article, similar to a News & Views piece. It has its\r\n  own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context\r\n  and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of\r\n  the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references\r\n  (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial\r\n  correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be\r\n  published by <i>%(appname)s</i>.<br />\r\n  4-\r\n  <b\r\n    >to declare that you have no conflict of interest with the authors or the\r\n    content of the article.</b\r\n  >\r\n  Indeed, you should not handle articles written by close colleagues (with whom\r\n  I have published in the last four years, with whom I have received joint\r\n  funding in the last four years, or with whom I am currently writing a\r\n  manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal), or written by family members,\r\n  friends, or anyone for whom bias might affect the nature of my evaluation. See\r\n  the <a href="%(ethicsurl)s">code of ethical conduct</a>. Bear in mind that if\r\n  you do not respect these commitments, the managing board of\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> reserves the right to pass responsibility for the\r\n  evaluation of this article to someone else.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>%(addNote)s Thank you for your help.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
23	#RecommenderSuggestedArticleReminder	default	%(appname)s: Request to act as a recommender for a preprint (reminder)	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  A few days ago, you were suggested as a recommender for a preprint entitled\r\n  <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s (DOI %(articleDoi)s). You can\r\n  obtain information about this request and accept or decline this invitation by\r\n  following this link <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging\r\n  on to the <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Requests for input —> Do\r\n  you agree to initiate a recommendation?' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding\r\n  reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews),\r\n  and may lead to the recommendation of the preprint after several rounds of\r\n  reviews. The evaluation forms the basis of the decision to ‘Revise’,\r\n  ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint. A preprint recommended by\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘classic’\r\n  articles published in peer-reviewed journals.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If after one or several rounds of review, you decide to recommend this\r\n  preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation” that will have its own DOI\r\n  and be published by <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND. The\r\n  recommendation is a short article, similar to a News & Views piece. It has its\r\n  own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context\r\n  and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of\r\n  the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references\r\n  (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial\r\n  correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be\r\n  published by <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If you agree to handle this preprint, you will be responsible for managing the\r\n  evaluation process until you reach a final decision (i.e. to recommend or\r\n  reject this preprint). You will be able to invite, through the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website, reviewers included in the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> database or from your own network.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Details about the recommendation process can be found here\r\n  <a href="%(helpurl)s">%(helpurl)s</a>. You can also watch this short video:\r\n  <a href="https://youtu.be/u5greO-q8-M"\r\n    >How to start and manage a preprint recommendation</a\r\n  >.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Thanks again for your help.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
25	#RecommenderThankForPostprint	default	%(appname)s: Thank you for initiating a recommendation!	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  You have decided to recommend a postprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b>. To\r\n  view and/or manage your recommendation, please follow this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or logging onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —> Your\r\n  recommendations of postprints' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you in advance for writing this recommendation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
26	#RecommenderThankForPreprint	default	%(appname)s: Thank you for initiating a recommendation!	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  You have agreed to be the recommender handling the preprint entitled\r\n  <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s (DOI %(articleDoi)s). Thank you\r\n  very much for your contribution.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  <b\r\n    >We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review\r\n    this preprint within the next 24 h</b\r\n  >, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week\r\n  if necessary, until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this\r\n  preprint within three weeks. We thank you in advance for respecting this\r\n  commitment.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Invitations to review can be sent using this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a>. You can also log on to the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to 'Your contributions —> Preprints you are\r\n  handling' in the top menu, and click on the 'choose a reviewer' button.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  The reviews you receive should guide your decision –\r\n  <b>within 10 days of receiving the last review</b> – as to whether to\r\n  ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a\r\n  “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short\r\n  article, similar to a News & Views piece. It has its own title, contains\r\n  between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the\r\n  preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also\r\n  be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the\r\n  preprint being recommended). All editorial correspondence (reviews, your\r\n  decisions, authors' replies) relating to the preprint will also be published\r\n  by <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n
27	#RecommenderThankForPreprintParallelSubmission	default	%(appname)s: Thank you for initiating a recommendation!	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  You have agreed to be the recommender handling the preprint entitled\r\n  <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s (DOI %(articleDoi)s). Thank you\r\n  very much for your contribution.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  <b\r\n    >We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review\r\n    this preprint within the next 24 h</b\r\n  >, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week\r\n  if necessary, until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this\r\n  preprint within three weeks. We thank you in advance for respecting this\r\n  commitment.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Invitations to review can be sent using this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a>. You can also log on to the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to 'Your contributions —> Preprints you are\r\n  handling' in the top menu, and click on the 'choose a reviewer' button.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  The reviews you receive should guide your decision –\r\n  <b>within 10 days of receiving the last review</b> – as to whether to\r\n  ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a\r\n  “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short\r\n  article, similar to a News & Views piece. It has its own title, contains\r\n  between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the\r\n  preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also\r\n  be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the\r\n  preprint being recommended). All editorial correspondence (reviews, your\r\n  decisions, authors' replies) relating to the preprint will also be published\r\n  by <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  The authors have chosen to submit elsewhere in parallel. As there is a chance\r\n  that the manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere and consequently the\r\n  authors might abandon the process at <i>%(appname)s</i>, we have the following\r\n  mechanism to ensure reviewers’ work is respected and documented. If the\r\n  authors abandon the process at <i>%(appname)s</i> after reviewers have written\r\n  their reports, you should post the reviewers' reports on the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website as recognition of the reviewers' work and in order\r\n  to enable critical discussion. Note that there remains the outcome of\r\n  rejection by you, wherein reports are not made public.\r\n</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>
2	#AdminNewUser	default	%(appname)s: A new user has signed up	\N	<p>Dear administrators,</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">A new user has joined <em>%(appname)s</em>: %(userTxt)s (%(userMail)s).</p>\r\n<p>If this user can act as a recommender, you <a href="https://agora-quiz.education">should</a> change his/her status.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
30	#RecommenderCoRecommenderDeclined	default	%(appname)s: co-recommender declined the recommendation	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  %(contributorPerson)s has declined your invitation to co-sign the\r\n  recommendation of the postprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You may check your recommendation by following this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging to the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —> Your\r\n  recommendations of postprints' in the top menu. You may invite another\r\n  recommender to co-sign your recommendation if you wish.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for writing this recommendation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
32	#RecommenderReviewDeclined	default	%(appname)s: Request to review declined	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  %(reviewerPerson)s has declined your invitation to review the preprint\r\n  entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s (DOI %(articleDoi)s).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You will need to find another reviewer to obtain the two high-quality reviews\r\n  required. You can invite additional reviewers by following this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —> Preprints you\r\n  are handling' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for managing this evaluation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
31	#RecommenderReviewConsidered	default	%(appname)s: Request to review accepted	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  %(reviewerPerson)s has accepted your invitation to review the preprint\r\n  entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s (DOI %(articleDoi)s),\r\n  and has been sent a message indicating that this review must be posted or\r\n  uploaded on the <i>%(appname)s</i> website before %(dueTime)s.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You will receive a message notifying you of the posting of this review. If the\r\n  review is not posted by the deadline, you can send the reviewer a reminder by\r\n  following this link <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging\r\n  on to the <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —>\r\n  Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for managing this evaluation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
28	#RecommenderCoRecommenderAgreement	default	%(appname)s: co-recommender agreed with the recommendation of the postprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  %(contributorPerson)s has agreed with the recommendation of the postprint\r\n  entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You may check your recommendation by following this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —> Your\r\n  recommendations of postprints' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for writing this recommendation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
29	#RecommenderCoRecommenderConsiderated	default	%(appname)s: co-recommender accepted the recommendation	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  %(contributorPerson)s has accepted to co-sign the recommendation of the\r\n  postprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You may check your recommendation by following this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging on to the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —> Your\r\n  recommendations of postprints' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for writing this recommendation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
33	#ReviewerReviewCompleted	default	%(appname)s: Review completed	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  The review by %(reviewerPerson)s of the preprint entitled\r\n  <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> is now available.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  You can view and/or upload this review and manage your recommendation by\r\n  following this link <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging\r\n  onto the <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —>\r\n  Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  <b>If all the reviews have now been completed</b> and returned,\r\n  <b>we now expect you</b>, according to your commitment as a recommender of the\r\n  preprint, <b>to make a decision within a few days</b>. If you need more time,\r\n  please let us know by return mail.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  We remind you that this decision must be: ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’\r\n  the preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  If you decide to recommend this preprint, you will need to write a\r\n  "recommendation" that will have its own DOI and will be published by\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short\r\n  article, similar to a News & Views piece. It has its own title, contains\r\n  between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the\r\n  preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also\r\n  be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the\r\n  preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your\r\n  decisions, authors’ replies) relating to the preprint will also be published\r\n  by <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for managing this evaluation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
34	#ReviewerReviewReopened	default	%(appname)s: Review modification	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  %(recommenderPerson)s, the recommender managing the evaluation process for the\r\n  preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s has made your\r\n  review concerning this preprint available for modification.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You can now access this review, and edit it if necessary.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You can view and edit your reviews by following this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —> My reviews' in\r\n  the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for agreeing to review this preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
35	#ReviewerThankForReviewAcceptation	default	%(appname)s: Thank you for agreeing to review a preprint!	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  Thank you very much for agreeing to review the preprint entitled\r\n  <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s (DOI %(articleDoi)s). Please\r\n  complete your review within three weeks, hence before <b>%(dueTime)s</b>. If\r\n  this dealine is too short, please let me know as soon as possible. Otherwise,\r\n  thank you in advance for respecting this deadline.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or log onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to ‘Your contributions —> Your reviews’ in\r\n  the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on\r\n  the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review\r\n  later;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  or\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  2) save and send me your review by clicking on the ‘Save & submit your review’\r\n  button.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for\r\n  modification or completion by clicking on ‘Your contributions —> Your reviews’\r\n  in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the\r\n  corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save & submit your review’\r\n  button to send your completed review to me.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  I look forward to reading your review.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  <span style="padding-left:1in;">The recommender, %(recommenderPerson)s</span>\r\n</p>\r\n
36	#ReviewerThankForReviewDone	default	%(appname)s: Thank you for evaluating a preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  Thank you for evaluating the preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by\r\n  %(articleAuthors)s. Your evaluation has been sent to the recommender\r\n  (%(recommenderPerson)s) handling this preprint. Your contribution is greatly\r\n  appreciated.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You can use this message as proof of your work for <i>%(appname)s</i> and you\r\n  can view your review at <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a>. Your\r\n  review, together with the other reviews of this preprint, will guide the\r\n  decision of the recommender (%(recommenderPerson)s) as to whether to ‘Revise’,\r\n  ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ this preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Remember that if the recommender eventually comes to a favorable conclusion,\r\n  all of the editorial correspondence (reviews, including yours, the decisions\r\n  reached by the recommender, and the authors’ replies) and a recommendation\r\n  text will be published by <i>%(appname)s</i>, under the license CC-BY-ND. If,\r\n  after one or several rounds of review, the recommender eventually rejects the\r\n  preprint, the editorial correspondence will be sent to the authors but will\r\n  NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the\r\n  procedure.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  %(parallelText)s If the recommender asks the authors to revise their preprint,\r\n  he/she may invite you to evaluate their responses and the changes they have\r\n  made to the preprint. If required, we therefore hope that you will be willing\r\n  to take part in a second round of review.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  If you decided NOT to remain anonymous, your name will be passed on to the\r\n  authors and, if the recommender decides to recommend this preprint, your name\r\n  will be visible and associated with your review on the %(appname)s website. If\r\n  you wish to change your mind and remain anonymous, please send a message to\r\n  %(contactMail)s, to let the members of the Managing Board know (they will make\r\n  the necessary changes).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  In the meantime, thank you again for conducting this evaluation. We really\r\n  appreciate it.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Best wishes,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n
37	#ReviewersArticleRecommended	default	%(appname)s: Decision on preprint you reviewed	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  The article that you kindly reviewed for <i>%(appname)s</i> is now\r\n  recommended. The recommendation of this article - along with your reviews - is\r\n  now posted on <i>%(appname)s</i> website.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="%(recommDOI)s">%(recommDOI)s</a></p>\r\n<p>And there: <a href="%(linkRecomm)s">%(linkRecomm)s</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you\r\n  are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc... Thanks again for\r\n  reviewing this article for <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
38	#ReviewersArticleStatusChanged	default	%(appname)s: Decision on preprint you reviewed	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  You have agreed to review the preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b>. The\r\n  status of this preprint is now: %(articleStatus)s. To view your review, the\r\n  reviews of the other referees and the decision taken by the recommender,\r\n  please follow this link <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or login\r\n  to the <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to 'Your contributions —> My reviews'\r\n  in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you for the time spent evaluating this preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
39	#ReviewersArticleCancellation	default	%(appname)s: About our request to act as reviewer for a preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  The submission of the preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by\r\n  %(articleAuthors)s has been cancelled by the author. Therefore, the\r\n  recommendation process is closed. Thank you anyway for your help.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  <span style="padding-left:1in;">%(recommenderPerson)s</span>\r\n</p>\r\n
40	#ReviewerReviewInvitation	default	%(appname)s: Invitation to review a preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  I have agreed to handle the evaluation of a preprint entitled\r\n  <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> by %(articleAuthors)s, for potential recommendation by\r\n  <i>%(appdesc)s</i> (<i>%(appname)s</i>). This article can be visualized and\r\n  downloaded at the following address (doi %(articleDoi)s).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  At first glance, this preprint appears to me to be potentially interesting,\r\n  but I would like to have your expert opinion. I would therefore like to invite\r\n  you to review this preprint for <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If you have already reviewed a previous version of this MS, please consider\r\n  this message as an invitation to review a new version of the preprint for a\r\n  new round of evaluation.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The evaluation process should guide the decision as to whether to ‘Revise’,\r\n  ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint. A preprint recommended by\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> is an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’\r\n  article published in a peer-reviewed journals.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If I eventually reach a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence\r\n  (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text\r\n  will be published by <i>%(appname)s</i>, under the license CC-BY-ND. If after\r\n  one or several rounds of review, I eventually reject the preprint, the\r\n  editorial correspondence (and specifically your review) will be sent to the\r\n  authors but will NOT published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage\r\n  in the procedure.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Please let me know as soon as possible whether you are willing to accept my\r\n  invitation to review this article, or whether you would prefer to decline, by\r\n  clicking on the link below or by logging on to the <i>%(appname)s</i> website\r\n  and going to 'Requests for input —> Do you agree to review a preprint?' in the\r\n  top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If you agree, you will then be able to copy/paste, write or upload your review\r\n  onto the <i>%(appname)s</i> website.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Thanks in advance for your help.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  <span style="padding-left:1in;">%(recommenderPerson)s</span>\r\n</p>\r\n
41	#SubmitterAwaitingSubmission	default	%(appname)s: Decision concerning your submission	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  Your article, entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b>, has now been reviewed. The\r\n  referees' comments and the recommender’s decision are shown below. As you can\r\n  see, the recommender found your article very interesting, but suggests certain\r\n  revisions.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We shall, in principle, be happy to recommend your article as soon as it has\r\n  been revised in response to the points raised by the referees.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  When revising your article, we remind you that:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  1) Data must be available to readers, either in the text or through an open\r\n  data repository such as Zenodo (free), Dryad (to pay) or some other\r\n  institutional repository. Data must be reusable, thus metadata or accompanying\r\n  text must carefully describe the data;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  2) Details on quantitative analyses (e.g., data treatment and statistical\r\n  scripts in R, bioinformatic pipeline scripts, etc.) and details concerning\r\n  simulations (scripts, codes) must be available to readers in the text, as\r\n  appendices, or through an open data repository, such as Zenodo, Dryad or some\r\n  other institutional repository. The scripts or codes must be carefully\r\n  described so that they can be reused;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  3) Details on experimental procedures must be available to readers in the text\r\n  or as appendices;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  4) Authors must have no financial conflict of interest relating to the\r\n  article. The article must contain a "Conflict of interest disclosure"\r\n  paragraph before the reference section containing this sentence: "The authors\r\n  of this article declare that they have no financial conflict of interest with\r\n  the content of this article.";\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  5) This disclosure has to be completed by a sentence indicating, if\r\n  appropriate, that some of the authors are PCI recommenders: “XY is one of the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> recommenders.”.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  When your revised article is ready, please:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  1) Upload the new version of your manuscript onto your favorite open archive;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  2) Follow this link <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or logging\r\n  onto the <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to 'your contributions' section and\r\n  then to 'Your submitted preprints' subsection in the top menu;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  3) Make your changes to the title, summary, link to the article (or its DOI)\r\n  and keywords if necessary by clicking on the 'Edit Article' button. If not\r\n  already done, you also need to upload a picture or an illustration for which\r\n  you own the rights – this picture will be used to illustrate your article, if\r\n  recommended;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  4) Write, copy/paste or upload (as a PDF file) your reply to the recommender's\r\n  and reviewers' comments by clicking on the 'Write, edit or upload your reply\r\n  to recommender' button. You can also upload (as a PDF file) a revised version\r\n  of your article, with the modifications indicated in TrackChanges mode;\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  5) When you are ready to submit your new version, click on the 'Save & submit\r\n  your reply' button.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Once the recommender has read the revised version, he/she may decide to\r\n  recommend it directly, in which case the editorial correspondence (reviews,\r\n  recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be\r\n  published by <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Alternatively, other rounds of reviews may be needed before the recommender\r\n  reaches a favorable conclusion. He/she may also reject your article, in which\r\n  case the reviews and decision will be sent to you, but they will not be\r\n  published or publicly released by <i>%(appname)s</i>. They will be safely\r\n  stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will\r\n  be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you in advance for submitting your revised version.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
42	#SubmitterCancelledSubmission	default	%(appname)s: Cancellation of your submission	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  The submission of your preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> has been\r\n  cancelled. We respect your decision, and hope that you will submit other\r\n  preprints to <i>%(appdesc)s</i> (<i>%(appname)s</i>) in the near future.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If your manuscript was sent to reviewers and evaluated, we will add a link to\r\n  the reports on our progress log page. This is because you chose the parallel\r\n  submission option and we do not wish to waste the effort that went into\r\n  evaluating your work. This provides reviewers a possibility to claim credit\r\n  for their evaluation work and, in addition to being useful to your team, we\r\n  hope the reports are useful discussion points for other researchers in the\r\n  field.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
43	#SubmitterNotConsideredSubmission	default	%(appname)s: Decision concerning your submission	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  You have submitted your preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> to\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Unfortunately, no recommender has initiated the evaluation of your preprint\r\n  since the request was made %(unconsider_limit_days)s days ago. This does not\r\n  mean that your preprint is not of sufficient quality and/or interest. However,\r\n  we suggest that you do not wait any longer for a return from us at this stage.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We are sorry to bring disappointing news and hope that that you will consider\r\n  submitting other preprints to <i>%(appname)s</i> in the future.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
44	#SubmitterParallelPreprintUnderConsideration	default	%(appname)s: Consideration of your preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  You have submitted your preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> to\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i>. We are pleased to inform you that a\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> recommender has initiated the evaluation process.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  At this stage of the process, your article will be sent to several referees,\r\n  to ensure that at least two high-quality reviews are obtained. Based on this\r\n  review, the recommender will reject, recommend or ask you to modify your\r\n  article and to respond to the questions and points raised by the reviewers.\r\n  The mean time to this first decision is about %(recomm_limit_days)s days.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your\r\n  preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence\r\n  (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text\r\n  will be published by <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND. If\r\n  recommended by <i>%(appname)s</i>, your preprint will become an article that\r\n  may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed\r\n  journal.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the\r\n  reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published\r\n  or publicly released by <i>%(appname)s</i>. They will be safely stored in our\r\n  database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by\r\n  e-mail at each stage of the procedure.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You have selected the option of submitting elsewhere in parallel. We encourage\r\n  you to finish the peer-review process with <i>%(appname)s</i> even if your\r\n  manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere. Please note that if this\r\n  does happen and you abandon the process with <i>%(appname)s</i> after\r\n  reviewers have contributed their time toward evaluation, we will post the\r\n  reviewers' reports on the <i>%(appname)s</i> website as recognition of the\r\n  reviewers' work and in order to enable critical discussion. If you do not\r\n  agree with this, please consider cancelling your submission now, before\r\n  reviewers are recruited.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  To view your recommendation request, please follow this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or log onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to 'Your contributions —> Your submitted\r\n  preprints' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for your submission.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
45	#SubmitterParallelPreprintSubmitted	default	%(appname)s: Submission of your preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  Thank you for submitting your preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b>, to\r\n  <i>%(appdesc)s</i> (<i>%(appname)s</i>).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If you have not already done so, you can suggest recommenders who could\r\n  initiate the evaluation of your preprint. A recommender is very similar to a\r\n  journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and\r\n  making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend\r\n  your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Please remember that <i>%(appname)s</i> is under no obligation to consider\r\n  your preprint. We cannot guarantee that your preprint will be reviewed, but\r\n  all possible efforts will be made to make this possible. You will be notified\r\n  by e-mail if a <i>%(appname)s</i> recommender decides to start the peer-review\r\n  process for your preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your\r\n  preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence\r\n  (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text\r\n  will be published by <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND. If\r\n  recommended by <i>%(appname)s</i>, your preprint will become an article that\r\n  may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed\r\n  journal.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the\r\n  reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published\r\n  or publicly released by <i>%(appname)s</i>. They will be safely stored in our\r\n  database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by\r\n  e-mail at each stage of the procedure.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You have selected the option of submitting elsewhere in parallel. We encourage\r\n  you to finish the peer-review process with <i>%(appname)s</i> even if your\r\n  manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere. Please note that if this\r\n  does happen and you abandon the process with <i>%(appname)s</i> after\r\n  reviewers have contributed their time toward evaluation, we will post the\r\n  reviewers' reports on the <i>%(appname)s</i> website as recognition of the\r\n  reviewers' work and in order to enable critical discussion. If you do not\r\n  agree with this, please consider cancelling your submission now, before\r\n  reviewers are recruited.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  To view your recommendation request, please follow this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or log onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to 'Your contributions —> Your submitted\r\n  preprints' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for your submission.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
46	#SubmitterPreprintStatusChanged	default	%(appname)s: Change in the status of your preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  The status of your preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> has changed from\r\n  "%(tOldStatus)s" to "%(tNewStatus)s".\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You can view, edit or cancel your request by following this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and going to 'Your contributions —> Your submitted\r\n  preprints' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for your submission.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
47	#SubmitterPreprintUnderConsideration	default	%(appname)s: Consideration of your preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  You have submitted your preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> to\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i>. We are pleased to inform you that a\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> recommender has initiated the evaluation process.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  At this stage of the process, your article will be sent to several referees,\r\n  to ensure that at least two high-quality reviews are obtained. Based on this\r\n  review, the recommender will reject, recommend or ask you to modify your\r\n  article and to respond to the questions and points raised by the reviewers.\r\n  The mean time to this first decision is about %(recomm_limit_days)s days.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We remind you that this preprint must not be submitted for publication\r\n  elsewhere until its evaluation by <i>%(appname)s</i> is complete.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your\r\n  preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence\r\n  (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text\r\n  will be published by <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license CC-BY-ND. If\r\n  recommended by <i>%(appname)s</i> your preprint will become an article that\r\n  may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed\r\n  journal.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the\r\n  reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published\r\n  or publicly released by <i>%(appname)s</i>. They will be safely stored in our\r\n  database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by\r\n  e-mail at each stage in the procedure.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  To view or cancel your recommendation request, please follow this link\r\n  <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or logging onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to 'Your contributions —> Your submitted\r\n  preprints' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for your submission.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
48	#SubmitterRecommendedPreprint	default	%(appname)s: Recommendation of your preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  We are pleased to inform you that the peer-review process concerning your\r\n  article entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> has reached a favorable conclusion. A\r\n  recommendation text written by the recommender has now been published by\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i>. The editorial correspondence (reviews, author’s responses\r\n  and recommender’s decisions) has also been published by <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="%(doiRecomm)s">%(doiRecomm)s</a></p>\r\n<p>And there: <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n  You will find there, the reference to your recommendation and that of your\r\n  recommended preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you\r\n  are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc...\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If you intend to submit your article to a PCI friendly journal (see the list\r\n  here https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/) together with the PCI\r\n  evaluations, you should send us a email at %(contact)s with the name of the\r\n  journal(s). We can then provide you with specific informations about this\r\n  journals if we have some.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Thank you for using <i>%(appname)s</i>. We hope that you will submit other\r\n  preprints in the future and will tell your colleagues about\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
49	#SubmitterRejectedSubmission	default	%(appname)s: Decision concerning your submission	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  Your preprint entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b> has been evaluated by at least\r\n  two referees. On the basis of these reviews, we regret to inform you that the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> recommender in charge of this evaluation has decided not to\r\n  recommend it.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The reviews and the recommender’s decision are shown below. These reviews and\r\n  the decision will not be published or publicly released by <i>%(appname)s</i>.\r\n  They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board\r\n  has access.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We are sorry to bring disappointing news and hope that you will consider\r\n  submitting other preprints to <i>%(appname)s</i> in the future.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for your submission.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
50	#SubmitterPreprintSubmitted	default	%(appname)s: Submission of your preprint	\N	Dear %(destPerson)s,\r\n<p>\r\n  Thank you for your submission, on behalf of all the authors, of your preprint\r\n  entitled <b>%(articleTitle)s</b>, to <i>%(appdesc)s</i> (<i>%(appname)s</i>).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  We remind you that this preprint must not be published or submitted for\r\n  publication elsewhere. If this preprint is sent out for review, you must not\r\n  submit it to a journal until the evaluation process is complete (ie until it\r\n  has been rejected or recommended by <i>%(appname)s</i>).\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If you have not already done so, you need to suggest recommenders who could\r\n  initiate the evaluation of your preprint. A recommender is very similar to a\r\n  journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and\r\n  making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend\r\n  your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Please remember that <i>%(appname)s</i> is under no obligation to consider\r\n  your preprint. We cannot guarantee that your preprint will be reviewed, but\r\n  all possible efforts will be made to make this possible. By submitting your\r\n  preprint to <i>%(appname)s</i>, you agree to wait until a recommender\r\n  initiates the evaluation process, within a maximum of\r\n  %(unconsider_limit_days)s days. You will be notified by e-mail if a\r\n  recommender of the <i>%(appname)s</i> decides to start the peer-review process\r\n  for your preprint.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  If after one or several rounds of reviews, the <i>%(appname)s</i> recommender\r\n  handling your preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial\r\n  correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a\r\n  recommendation text will be published by <i>%(appname)s</i> under the license\r\n  CC-BY-ND. If recommended by <i>%(appname)s</i> your preprint would become an\r\n  article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a\r\n  peer-reviewed journal.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the\r\n  reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published\r\n  or publicly released by <i>%(appname)s</i>. They will be safely stored in our\r\n  database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by\r\n  e-mail at each stage in the procedure.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  %(parallelText)s To view or cancel your recommendation request, please follow\r\n  this link <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or logging onto the\r\n  <i>%(appname)s</i> website and go to 'Your contributions —> Your submitted\r\n  preprints' in the top menu.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  We thank you again for your submission.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  Yours sincerely,\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n  The Managing Board of <i>%(appname)s</i>\r\n</p>\r\n
5	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticle	default	%(appname)s: Your co-recommendation of a %(articlePrePost)s	\N	<p>Dear %(destPerson)s,</p>\r\n<p>A peer-review evaluation of a preprint by <em>%(articleAuthors)s</em> and entitled <strong>%(articleTitle)s</strong> (DOI %(articleDoi)s) is currenlty handled by the recommender %(recommenderPerson)s. This recommender declared you as a co-recommender and, as such, as a co-author of the recommendation if he/she decides to recommend this preprint. The reviews and the recommendation text can be viewed by clicking on this link: <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging onto the <em>%(appname)s</em> website and going to 'Your contributions —&gt; Your co-recommendations' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that a preprint is recommended if, and only if it is scientifically valid and of high quality and the code of conduct has been followed. The decision to recommend a preprint must be based on high-quality reviews. We also remind you that, the recommendation text, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, decisions, your recommendation and authors’ replies) will be published by <em>%(appname)s</em>. Being a co-recommender for this preprint means that you share full responsibility with the recommender for the public recommendation of this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to be a co-recommender of this preprint, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for this contribution to <em>%(appname)s</em>.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of <em>%(appname)s</em></p>
4	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticleAlreadyPublished	default	%(appname)s: Your co-recommendation of a %(articlePrePost)s	\N	<p>Dear %(destPerson)s,</p>\r\n<p>A recommendation text for the %(articlePrePost)s by <em>%(articleAuthors)s</em> and entitled <strong>%(articleTitle)s</strong> (DOI %(articleDoi)s) is under consideration. You have been declared as a co-recommender of this %(articlePrePost)s. You can view the recommendation by following this link <a href="%(linkTarget)s">%(linkTarget)s</a> or by logging onto the <em>%(appname)s</em> website and going to 'Your contributions —&gt; Your co-recommendations' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We are currently handling this recommendation; it will probably be rapidly posted on the <em>%(appname)s</em> website.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to co-author this recommendation, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for co-writing this recommendation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of <em>%(appname)s</em></p>
